{
  "stem": "3952.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the happy one who grabbed it washed the bone, and ate it until there was-- it was possible to eat.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when it was too hard-- the part that was so hard that you couldn't eat-- we burned it, and he continued to-- to eat it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So you didn't know it was a bone of a human being, or an animal, or how old it was.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You didn't care.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You were so hungry that you would-- you would just eat everything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But we were so religious that even after the war, when we ate those conserves, those cans of meat, and it was not kosher-- it was whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't even know what it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't care what it was, but I would make a blessing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In my-- in my mind, I would make a blessing, because we make a blessing before eating something and after eating something, because the Talmud has it that everything belongs to God.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if you take something without-- without saying a blessing, then you are kind of stealing from God.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you can't do that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So you say the blessing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By the blessing, you acquire it, and it belongs to you, and then you can eat it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So even after eating non-kosher food, I would make the blessing, or when I drank a little water, I would make that certain blessing before-- before drinking it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember, we were very close to Elie Wiesel, who is now a very famous person, maybe the most famous Jew-- non-religious Jew-- When did you first meet him?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we were together in school in Sighet.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- we were like close friends, very-- like the two more-- shall we say the best-- better scholars.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
